@startuml validation-layer-class
' Validation-boundary layer (Pass A, REV 2) for spartan-erp-engine.
' SCOPE: Zod at the FIXED, code-known boundaries ONLY.
'   - request envelopes (handler)        -> reject malformed input -> 400
'   - the doctype def (the "meta-schema") -> structural-only, before installer writes
'   - env (cold-start fail-fast)
' depends_on / mandatory_depends_on is DEFERRED out of Pass A (see ADR rev 2 §3) and is
' NOT drawn as active design here.
' Conservative PlantUML: classes (modules-as-objects) + relationships only.

title Validation Layer (Pass A, rev 2) - Zod boundaries ONLY

' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
' Existing engine pieces this layer plugs into (shown for context, not re-designed)
' ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
package "api (existing)" {
  class "handler.handle()" as Handler {
    +handle({method,doctype,name,body,query,ctx}, store)
    --
    1st step already awaits ensure(doctype, store)
    NEW: validate request ENVELOPE via RequestSchemas
         after ensure(), before dispatch
  }
  class "service.js" as Service {
    createDoc / updateDoc / listDocs
    submitDoc / cancelDoc / transitionDoc
  }
}

package "runtime (existing)" {
  class "errors.ValidationError" as ValidationError {
    EngineError subclass -> 400 (statusFor, handler.js:10)
  }
  class "validate.validateAgainstMeta()" as ValidateMeta {
    reqd / Select / numeric / Check / unique
    --
    UNCHANGED in Pass A (depends_on deferred)
  }
}

package "meta (existing)" {
  class "installer.syncDoctype() / migrate()" as Installer {
    upsert tabDocType/tabDocField/tabDocPerm
    emitMigration (DDL -> file)
    --
    NEW: assertValidDef(def) as FIRST line (structural)
  }
  class "ddl.PG_TYPE_MAP" as DdlMap {
    frozen fieldtype -> pg type map
    --
    SINGLE SOURCE of the fieldtype enum (M1)
  }
}

package "infra (existing)" {
  class "SupabaseStore.fromEnv()" as SbStore
  class "PgAdmin.fromEnv()" as PgAdmin {
    keeps its OWN /DATABASE_URL/ check (B2)
  }
}

' ===========================================================================
' NEW MODULES (Pass A, rev 2)  src/validation/
' ===========================================================================
package "validation (NEW)  src/validation/" {

  ' --- (1a) request-envelope Zod schemas -------------------------------------
  class "request-schemas.js" as RequestSchemas <<zod const>> {
    +CreatePayloadSchema   record + refine(reject owner/docstatus/name) NO .strict()
    +UpdatePatchSchema     same as Create (reserved-key refine, NO .strict())
    +ActionBodySchema      object({action:string min1}).passthrough()
    +ListQuerySchema       coerce limit/offset/order + f_* passthrough
    --
    envelope-only: per-field rules stay meta-driven (validate.js)
  }

  ' --- (1b) the meta-schema: structural "schema for the meta" ----------------
  class "def-schema.js" as DefSchema <<zod const>> {
    +DocTypeDefSchema
    +DocFieldDefSchema   fieldtype enum, Link|Table => options STRING present
    +DocPermDefSchema    .passthrough() (tolerate stray doctype key, M2)
    +assertValidDef(def)
    --
    STRUCTURAL ONLY (B1): no cross-doctype existence check
    (that is loader.load N1, loader.js:112)
    enum = Object.keys(PG_TYPE_MAP).concat('Table')  (M1, no drift)
  }

  ' --- (1c) env schemas (TWO, separate) --------------------------------------
  class "env-schema.js" as EnvSchema <<zod const>> {
    +EnvSchema          SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
    +loadEnv(env)       -> {url, key}   (Supabase keys ONLY)
    +PgAdminEnvSchema   DATABASE_URL
    +loadPgAdminEnv(env) -> {databaseUrl}
    --
    throw PLAIN Error (NOT ValidationError) - operator/cold-start,
    never a client 400. Lazy (inside fromEnv), not import-time.
  }

  ' --- (1d) the single Zod->ValidationError bridge ---------------------------
  class "zod-bridge.js" as ZodBridge <<pure fn>> {
    +parseOrThrow(schema, value, label) : T
    catch !success -> throw ValidationError(label + flatten(msg))
    ONE place maps Zod -> ValidationError (DRY)
  }
}

' ===========================================================================
' Relationships
' ===========================================================================

' (1a) handler validates the request envelope before dispatch
Handler ..> RequestSchemas       : <<select by method/name/action>>
Handler ..> ZodBridge            : parseOrThrow(envelope, body|query)
Handler --> Service              : dispatch (after envelope OK)

' (1b) installer validates a doctype DEF (structural) before writing meta rows / DDL
Installer ..> DefSchema          : assertValidDef(def) [first line]
DefSchema ..> ZodBridge          : parseOrThrow(DocTypeDefSchema, def)
DefSchema ..> DdlMap             : enum = keys(PG_TYPE_MAP)+Table (M1)

' (1c) env validated lazily at cold start; the TWO loaders are distinct (B2)
SbStore  ..> EnvSchema           : loadEnv()        (Supabase keys)
PgAdmin  ..> EnvSchema           : loadPgAdminEnv() (DATABASE_URL only)

' all REQUEST/DEF Zod failures funnel through the one bridge to the one error type
ZodBridge ..> ValidationError    : throws  (-> 400)

note bottom of EnvSchema
  B2: PgAdmin does NOT route through loadEnv
  (which demands the two Supabase keys it
  doesn't need). It keeps its own DATABASE_URL
  check; thrown msg matches /DATABASE_URL/ so
  pg-admin.test.js stays green. Env failures
  are plain Error, not 400.
end note

note bottom of RequestSchemas
  B4: reserved-key reject is a REFINEMENT
  (owner|docstatus|name only), NOT .strict()
  (.strict would 400 every business field).
  Action + DocPerm schemas are .passthrough().
end note

note bottom of ValidateMeta
  depends_on / mandatory_depends_on DEFERRED
  out of Pass A (ADR rev 2 ss3). The whole
  chain (migration + boot-meta cols + installer
  write + loader read + validator) ships
  together in its own mini-pass. validate.js
  is UNCHANGED here.
end note

@enduml
